Quote:   It was now sunset, so we went aboard. The tide-waiter had come off, and the captain, afraid of his men running away, had put this functionary on guard; he was marching up and down the quarter-deck with the captain's double-barrelled gun on his shoulder, which he ... was swearing to shoot, ... and without the slightest compunction, [15] any man trying to leave the ship.
